# MAD converges to ~228µs as measurements stabilize, making the ±3.5σ threshold
# only ±800µs — too tight for CI runner variability. Even when the z-score
# exceeds 3.5σ, the failure is suppressed if the actual head deviation is
# below 10% of the tail median.
